The paper discusses the development of an ethical decision-making system for autonomous robots, which involves the use of a "consequence engine" to assess the likely outcomes of actions and select the most ethical choices. This topic is closely related to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO), as well as ethics (cs.ET) and software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of ensuring the correctness and reliability of the system. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential security risks associated with autonomous systems, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER).
